fields.headline: HIV Self-testing (HIVST) Project
fields.content:
We are currently distributing HIVST Kits in Muhoroni and Nyando sub-counties, Kisumu County. The kits are distributed free of charge primarily to male youths. The kits are oraquick, insti and sure check.
Ask for your preferred kit today.

fields.headline: Education Update
fields.content:
We are happy to report that the the Project for the Improvement of Educational Infrastructure - Construction of 8 modern classrooms and 8 pit latrines at Nyang Primary School in Muhoroni sub-county, Kisumu County is complete. 

We remained grateful to the community for embracing the project, the contractor for the good and timely work, our kind donor - The People of Japan and finally to the Almighty God for His wisdom and Knowledge.

fields.objective: Empowerment of youths and women to be productive in the society by provision of variety of trainings in economic, education, social and culture and also help create a youth to volunteer in community development work.
To protect the resources in our society and nurture the environment.
Advocate and create awareness on human and democratic rights, HIV/AIDS, drug and substance abuse, gender based violence, child protection and to promote community health and sanitation.
Creation of job opportunities targeting the less privileged women and youth in the community.

fields.about:
Arise and Shine Care Center is a Non-Profit Community Based Organization that was founded by a few youth  in April 2010, and  registered on 2nd November same year under the Ministry of Labor, Social Security and Services. 

The establishment of the C.B.O was conceived after a series of studies about the needs of women and youth was conducted.  The study revealed a serious lack of information among women and youth in our society, hence the creation of this organization to provide the vital information to youth. Pulling women and youth together and engaging them in various activities would enable them to arise from their state of hopelessness and/or lack of information and shine in the society, hence the name ARISE and SHINE.
fields.mission: To develop an effective organization with sustainable programs aimed at youth and women empowerment and promotion of community and family based sustainable intervention.
fields.vision: To be an organization with instrumental programs aimed at achieving an empowered community with avenues for sustainable development, reducing poverty index and giving top priority to the less privileged women in the community.

fields.project_description:
With the impacts of climate change, food insecurity has taken the center stage with many community members impacted negatively. With an effort to address this, our organization set up a Community and Youth Agricultural Resource Center Program (CARC) – climate smart farm in January 2020 with the aim of addressing food insecurity in the area and inspiring more people to establish similar projects and create employment for youth and women. This enables the community members to sustainably operate community-based climate smart farms. This project is located in Kiliti village, Ramula Sub-location, Ombeyi area in Muhoroni sub-county.

Our CARC project has continued to not only offer hands-on training to women and youth, but also provide employment to local women and youth besides supplying fresh vegetables to locals at affordable prices. The project currently employs 6 women and 2 men (youth). Our farming project has already inspired two groups which has established similar projects and are continuing to grow and supply vegetables to the local market. This has reduced the cost and uncertainties of doing business among some women since they do not now travel long distances in search of vegetables. This has greatly help in the face of COVID-19 where movement is restricted and market centers closed.

fields.project_name: Establishment of Ramula Health Center and Construction of Ramula Maternity Wing
fields.project_description:
Our organization established and registered Ramula Health Center in the year 2014. Access to affordable and better health care was a dream for many community members by then. Having established the center, mortality rate continued to be high due to lack of delivery facility in the community. This prompted us to seek support from the People of Japan through their GGP to construct a Maternity Wing towards reducing the high infant mortality rate. 

The Ramula Health Center has continued to offer health care services to hundreds of community members daily and has greatly reduced infant mortality rate. Our effort has also attracted the County Government of Kisumu to put us staffs’ houses, male ward, sunk a borehole for water supply and open up access road to the health center.

fields.project_name: Enhancing digital literacy among the youth
fields.project_description:
With the globalization, technology continues to play a critical role. We are training youths especially form four leavers and college students on basic and intermediate computer skills. This is enhancing their computer literacy. We are also providing a platform to college students who come to practice their computer skills while training youth and at the same time receiving some stipend. 

Our resource center is contributing to computer literacy among the youth, the skill which is currently preferred by many employers.

fields.project_name: Construction of Girls’ Dormitory at Ombeyi Secondary School
fields.project_description: With an effort to enhance girl child education, our organization through partnership with the Embassy of France to Kenya, constructed a dormitory block at Ombeyi Secondary School to enable more girls to board towards increasing their study time. The girl child education has for many years been overlooked and the girls are being burdened with a lot of unpaid care work reducing their study time. The construction of the dormitory has seen more girls board hence their performance enhanced.

fields.project_name: Improvement of Educational infrastructure at Nyang Primary school
fields.project_description:
In 2019, Arise and Shine Care Center sought  support from the People of Japan through the Grant Assistance for Grassroots  Human Security Projects (GGP) to improve the educational infrastructure of Nyang Primary School. The school had 8 classrooms which were all mud walled with most classrooms at the verge of collapsing; 2 temporary pit latrines which were insufficient for the school’s population. The school is found in the remote areas of the sub-county surrounded by sugarcane plantations posing insecurity to the pupils. Parents in the area use a lot of resources to facilitate education of their children despite the prevailing high poverty levels in the areas.  

Through the support, we managed to construct 8 modern classrooms and 8 pit latrines for the school. This effort attracted contribution from the community which supported the project through fencing, construction administration block and additional 5 latrines.

The project has enhanced the educational status of the area.

fields.project_name: Community Resource Center (Provision of Social Services)
fields.project_description:
Our offices at Ombeyi center has continued to provide social services to community members. These include facilitating registration of self-help groups, youth groups, women groups and community-based organizations. We continue to support them in processing all the necessary documents and reduce the expenses that were initially incurred by the groups in traveling forth and back. Our resource center is continuing to provide support to these groups on sustainability and on leadership. 

Our team is conducting regular training to these social groups on their needs that ranges from and not limited to leadership and conflict management, business management, access to finances among others.

Our organization is supporting community conservation actions such as wetland protection, tree planting exercises and energy conservation. Human survival is dependent on the environment hence cleaner and healthier environment is vital. We continue to support women on cooking energy conservation measures towards reducing indoor air pollution and premature deaths. 

We have also established tree nursery towards supporting the forestation programmes.

HIV testing services are essential gateway to HIV Prevention, treatment, care and support services. The World Health Organization (WHO) and the Joint United Nations Programme on HIV/AID (UNAIDS) endorse and encourage universal access to knowledge of HIV status.  

Our organization in partnership with Population Services Kenya is carrying out HIV Self Testing project in Muhoroni sub-county, Kisumu County. The project is geared towards increasing HIV Self-test uptake among men aged 18 -34 years. This project is enabling youth to make informed personal decision concerning their health. We bring to you HIVST Kits that are internationally approved, tested and proven to offer 99% accuracy. The HIVST Kits are OraQuick, Insti and Sure Check. 

The project is engaging local youths as promoters and HTS Counselors. The male youth are now reached and they could know their HIV Status at their convenience.
